```class Solution {
    public String breakPalindrome(String palindrome) {
        char[] arr = palindrome.toCharArray();
        int n = arr.length;
        if (n == 1) return "";
        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
            if (arr[i] != 'a') {
                arr[i] = 'a';
                return new String(arr);
            }
        }
        arr[n - 1] = 'b';
        return new String(arr);
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: We iterate through the first half of the palindrome, replacing the first non-'a' character with 'a'. If we reach the end of the first half without finding a non-'a' character, we replace the last character with 'b' to make the string not a palindrome.

